<P>A PERSONAL TESTIMONY</P>

<P>Let this old cop relate one of many recent, memorable meetings I've
had with fellow patriot Police Officers and Guardsmen. I was a guest speaker
at the Seattle, Washington Preparedness Expo in 1991, which drew a crowd
of 5,000 plus concerned Americans. At each of my talks there were many
fine federal, state and local police officers and military persons in the
audience. I was privileged to meet a number of these good patriot Officers
and to be able to speak with them after my speeches.</P>

<P>I recall in particular two Officers who worked as partners for the local
